THE MIGRANT SHIPWRECK NEAR GREECE IS A HORRIBLE TRAGEDY. BUT IT WASN'T AN ACCIDENT.

Early last Wednesday, a devastating incident unfolded off the coast of P├нlos, Greece, as a fishing boat, overburdened with people seeking refuge in Europe, tragically sank. Reports indicate that an astounding number of approximately 750 individuals were onboard the ill-fated vessel. Despite the valiant efforts of the Greek coast guard, who managed to rescue 104 survivors, the grim reality remains that 78 lives have been confirmed lost, and an alarming 560 individuals are still unaccounted for, presumed drowned. The magnitude of this catastrophe has prompted EU officials to label it as the worst-ever tragedy witnessed in the Mediterranean.

However, what makes this heart-wrenching shipwreck all the more distressing is the undeniable truth that it was not an isolated incident or a stroke of misfortune. Instead, it is a direct consequence of the prevailing practices and regulations enforced by Greek and EU authorities, rendering the act of entering Europe and seeking asylum increasingly unattainable. These stringent measures have inadvertently forced desperate individuals to resort to riskier and more perilous routes, endangering their lives in the process. It is a grim reflection of the political decisions made over the years, which have transformed the Mediterranean into an unforgiving graveyard, claiming countless innocent lives.

This devastating event serves as a somber reminder of the urgent need to address the root causes of migration and reassess the policies that govern the movement of individuals in search of safety and a better future. It is imperative for governments, both within the EU and beyond, to recognize their shared responsibility in ensuring the protection and well-being of those fleeing violence, persecution, and economic hardship.

Pemerintah rencananya akan segera membuka layanan perjalanan gratis selama 3 bulan naik Kereta Cepat dari Stasiun Halim menuju Stasiun Tegalluar maupun sebaliknya.

Menteri Perhubungan Budi Karya Sumadi mengungkapkan program ini akan berjalan setelah Kereta Cepat Jakarta-Bandung diluncurkan pada 18 Agustus 2023. 

Setelah itu, PT Kereta Cepat Indonesia China (KCIC) akan membuat program dengan memberikan kesempatan cuma-cuma alias gratis bagi seluruh warga khususnya DKI Jakarta dan Bandung untuk naik kereta cepat. Hanya saja calon penumpang yang mengikuti program ini dibatasi.

"18 Agustus soft launch. Setelah itu penumpang gratis sampai Oktober. Penumpang akan dipilih," ungkap Budi Karya di Stasiun Kereta Cepat Halim, Jakarta, Kamis (22/6/2023).

Sebanyak 50 warga negara Indonesia (WNI) mendapat undangan haji dari Raja Salman. Pelepasan keberangkatan mereka ke Tanah Suci dilakukan di Hotel St. Regis Jakarta pada Rabu (21/6/2023), oleh Duta Besar Arab Saudi untuk Indonesia, Faisal Abdullah H. Amodi.

"Merupakan kebahagiaan bagi saya untuk turut serta hadir dalam acara pelepasan tamu undangan," ucap Duta Besar Arab Saudi dalam sambutannya.

Adanya undangan haji dari Raja Salman untuk jemaah haji terpilih dari berbagai penjuru dunia menunjukkan komitmen Kerajaan Arab Saudi, dalam memberikan pelayanan haji semaksimal mungkin.

Netflix has unveiled its long-awaited plans to crack down on the rampant sharing of passwords to make more users pay for its video streaming service as growth slows. It is a far cry from the company's famous 2017 tweet "Love is sharing a password". The US-based streaming company now says it will limit Australian viewership to people living in the same household. It will start sending emails to customers who share beyond their four walls today. Those who subscribe to Netflix's standard or premium plans - which cost $16.99 to $22.99 a month - will be able to allow another person living outside their household to use their password for an extra $8 a month. That is a $2.99 discount from the company's basic plan. Find the full story at the link in bio.

With Starlink's potential entry into the Indian market, it could pave the way for enhanced connectivity and new opportunities for businesses and individuals.

National Book Fair will be organised from June 24 to July 2 at the Gaiety Theater in #Shimla.

Today's chief-marketers are expected to separate signals from an unprecedented explosion in noise, to adapt to changing attitudes, behaviors and events in real-time, to react to the hijacking of their brand narratives in a moment by consumers, employees and, sometimes, their C-suite colleagues; to provide absolute certainty that every dollar invested will deliver a 1:1 return (also in real-time), when no such certainty exists but is still, often, the expectation of those for whom their understanding of marketing is (often) limited to the fact that they have been marketed to. What was once the singular province of a CMO who had oversight if not control of positioning, product, price, and promotion, is now (again, often but not always) spread like too much butter on a piece of toast. And this is the thing about brands today; they are built, sustained, and sometimes punched in the face by people who aren't the CMO. But such is life, marketing, and the decentralized nature of a CMO's influence in 2023.

Pemerintah Kota (Pemkot) Surabaya bakal membagi 20 ribu lebih bendera merah putih untuk masyarakat menjelang Hari Ulang Tahun (HUT) ke-78 Kemerdekaan Republik Indonesia (RI).

Upaya itu bentuk komitmen menyukseskan program pembagian 10 juta bendera merah putih yang dicanangkan Kementerian Dalam Negeri (Kemendagri) RI. Nantinya, seluruh Aparatur Sipil Negara (ASN) Surabaya diwajibkan menyumbang bendera merah putih.

тАЬJadi, Pemkot Surabaya sudah melakukan pengumpulan bendera merah putih dari ASN di lingkungan Pemkot Surabaya,тАЭ kata Maria Theresia Ekawati Rahayu Kepala Badan Kesatuan Bangsa dan Politik (Bakesbangpol) Kota Surabaya, Jumat (23/6/2023).

Kewajiban mengumpulkan bendera itu sudah tercantum dalam Surat Edaran (SE) Gerakan Pembagian Bendera Merah Putih Tahun 2023, yang ditandatangani oleh Ikhsan Sekda Kota Surabaya. Jumlah sumbangan itu disesuaikan dengan tingkat jabatan ASN.

тАЬAda yang per orang diminta menyumbangkan 45 bendera, ada yang 10 hingga lima bendera tergantung kelompok jabatannya masing-masing,тАЭ kata Yayuk sapaan akrabnya.

Total akan ada 24.524 Bendera Merah Putih yang dikumpulkan Pemkot Surabaya. Jumlah itu meningkat seribu lebih dibanding dengan tahun lalu.

Selain ASN, seluruh pelaku usaha dan juga BUMD di lingkungan Pemkot Surabaya juga diminta berpartisipasi dalam gerakan pembagian 10 juta Bendera Merah Putih tahun 2023 ini. Imbauan itu juga sudah disebarluaskan kepada pelaku usaha dan BUMD di lingkungan Pemkot Surabaya.

тАЬIni penting karena Bendera Merah Putih itu merupakan identitas, simbol, dan alat pemersatu masyarakat Indonesia,тАЭ katanya.

Puing-puing kapal selam wisata Titanic telah ditemukan oleh Penjaga Pantai Amerika Serikat (AS). Dengan adanya penemuan puing-puing tersebut, para tim pencari menyimpulkan bahwa semua penumpang telah tewas.

Penjaga pantai mengumumkan penemuan puing-puing tersebut pada hari Kamis (22/6/2023) kemarin. Diperkirakan, kapal selam bernama Titan tersebut mengalami тАЬledakan dahsyatтАЭ pada saat menyelam di perairan Samudra Atlantik, Minggu (18/6/2023).

Penemuan puing-puing besar yang berisi beberapa bagian kapal terlihat oleh kendaraan yang dioperasikan dari jarak jauh. Kendaraan tersebut menjelajahi dasar laut dekat lokasi bangkai kapal Titanic. Puing-puing yang ditemukan itu berada di 1.600 kaki atau 488 meter dari haluan Titanic.

Komisi Pemberantasan Korupsi (KPK) menyita 20 aset milik tersangka gratifikasi dan pencucian uang, Rafael Alun Trisambodo. Total aset yang disita senilai Rp 150 miliar. "KPK pada proses penyidikan perkara tersebut, sejauh ini telah melakukan penyitaan terhadap 20 bidang tanah dan bangunan milik tersangka kasus dugaan gratifikasi dan tindak pidana pencucian uang (TPPU), RAT selaku eks pejabat pada Direktorat Jenderal Pajak (DJP), Kementerian Keuangan (Kemenkeu)," kata Kabag Pemberitaan KPK Ali Fikri, dalam keterangannya, Kamis (22/6/2023).

Ali menuturkan penyitaan tersebut merupakan hasil dari penelusuran tim penyidik KPK. Dia menyebut, dari hasil penelusuran, penyitaan aset dilakukan di tiga kota.Ali menyebut nilai dari 20 aset tersebut sebesar Rp 150 miliar. "Adapun total dari 20 aset yang disita ini jumlahnya mencapai Rp 150 miliar," katanya. Dia menuturkan penyitaan aset itu merupakan langkah KPK dalam melakukan optimalisasi pemulihan aset pelaku tindak pidana korupsi. Dia menyebut hal itu sejalan dengan target KPK.

Sebelumnya, KPK telah menyita sejumlah aset milik Rafael Alun berupa properti. Aset yang disita itu disebut berada di Jawa Tengah. "Ini update ya, itu di salah satu provinsi istimewa di Jawa Tengah kita juga sudah menyita properti," kata Direktur Penyidikan KPK Brigjen Asep Guntur Rahayu. Asep mengatakan KPK juga masih mencari aset Bitcoin atau crypto currency milik Rafael. KPK hingga kini masih belum menemukan aset tersebut.

Korlantas tanggapi perintah Kapolri Jenderal Pol. Listyo Sigit Prabowo terkait pengkajian ulang uji praktik SIM beberapa waktu lalu. Mereka akan melakukan kajian untuk memastikan apakah tes zig-zag dan membentuk angka delapan yang biasa dilakukan masih relevan atau tidak.

Hal ini disampaikan Brigjen Pol. Yusri Yunus, Direktur Registrasi dan Identifikasi Kendaraan Bermotor (Diregidents) Korlantas Polri. Ia menyampaikan bahwa kajian tersebut akan dilakukan oleh kelompok kerja (pokja) yang mereka bentuk.

Tak hanya itu, pihaknya juga akan melakukan evaluasi dengan melihat proses pembuatan SIM di beberapa negara lain. Namun hingga semua pekerjaan selesai dilakukan maka ujian praktik tetap dilaksanakan seperti biasa.

Ia pun menegaskan bahwa ujian praktik SIM bertujuan untuk memastikan kompetensi dan keterampilan pengemudi. Hal ini penting untuk mencegah terjadinya kecelakaan lalu lintas yang dikhawatirkan terjadi.

Badan Legislasi (Baleg) Dewan Perwakilan Rakyat (DPR) Republik Indonesia (RI) menyepakati perpanjangan masa jabatan kepala desa (kades) menjadi sembilan tahun dan dapat dipilih dua kali. 

Kesepakatan tersebut disampaikan dalam Rapat Panitia Kerja (Panja) Penyusunan Rancangan Undang-undang (RUU) Perubahan Kedua Undang-undang (UU) Nomor 6 Tahun 2014 tentang Desa Baleg DPR, Kamis (23/6/2023). 

Ketua Baleg DPR RI Supratman Andi Agtas mengatakan bahwa usulan perpanjangan masa jabatan kades didasari oleh pertimbangan untuk menjaga stabilitas desa.

Pernyataan tersebut Supratman sampaikan usai mengikuti Rapat Panja RUU Desa di Kompleks Parlemen, Jakarta, Kamis. Dia menilai, gesekan akibat pemilihan kepala desa (Pilkades) sering mengganggu stabilitas desa. Menurut Supratman, gangguan stabilitas desa menimbulkan terganggunya pertumbuhan dan pembangunan di desa. Padahal desa seharusnya menjadi ujung tombak dari pertumbuhan ekonomi. Ia mengungkapkan, pihaknya tidak ingin terjadinya gesekan antar-masyarakat mengganggu stabilitas desa yang dapat berdampak pada terhambatnya pembangunan. (Wil_Kompas.com)

AKTUAL-INDONESIA : Kabar gembira bagi Pegawai negeri sipil alias PNS, karena libur bersama Idul Adha pada 28-30 Juni mendatang tidak akan mengurangi jatah cuti tahunan.

Sebelumnya, cuti bersama di kalangan PNS biasanya mengurangi jatah cuti tahunan.

Hari cuti bersama ditambahkan menyambut hari raya Idul Adha yang menjadi hari libur nasional di tanggal 29 Juni 2023. Dengan begitu, ada kesempatan libur panjang minggu depan karena tanggal 1 dan 2 Juli 2023 merupakan hari Sabtu dan Minggu.

Dalam Keputusan Presiden (KEPPRES) 24 tahun 2022 tentang cuti bersama Pegawai Aparatur Sipil Negara Tahun 2023, cuti bersama PNS tidak mengurangi hak cuti pegawai para abdi negara.

тАЬCuti bersama sebagaimana dimaksud pada diktum kesatu tidak mengurangi hak cuti tahunan Pegawai Aparatur Sipil Negara,тАЭ tulis beleid tersebut dikutip Kamis (22/6/2023).

The last date to file an Income Tax Return (ITR) for the 2022-23 fiscal year (assessment year 2023-24) is July 31.

It is advisable to submit the ITR before the due date to avoid last minute rush. Nowadays the process of e-file ITR has become simple and fast and can be done from the comfort of your home. But sometimes the process of filing an ITR can be a difficult one, especially for first-time applicants.

Here are a few key things new taxpayers should know before filing their ITR:

1. Get Form 16: Form 16 is a TDS (Tax Deducted at Source) certificate issued by an employer to salaried employees. This form contains all salary information that must be filled in when filing the income tax return. This contains details about the exemptions you have taken advantage of, your wages and the deductions you have applied for.

Nama mantan Gubernur DKI Jakarta, Ali Sadikin, diabadikan untuk menggantikan nama Jalan Kebon Sirih menjadi Jalan Ali Sadikin. Ini diusulkan Ketua DPRD DKI Jakarta,Prasetyo Edi Marsudi,yang minta Pemerintah Provinsi DKI menetapkan nama Ali Sadikin sebagai nama jalan tersebut dalam HUT ke-469 DKI Jakarta.

Hal tersebut disampaikan Prasetyo saat pidato rapat paripurna DPRD DKI, Kamis. "Kami minta eksekutif DKI agar nama Ali Sadikin diabadikan sebagai nama jalan menggantikan Jalan Kebon Sirih" kata Prasetyo. Menurut Prasetyo, Ali Sadikin merupakan salah satu gubernur yang berperan penting dalam membawa DKI Jakarta menjadi kota metropolitan.

Pemerintah melihat peluang agar proyek kereta cepat itu bisa diteruskan hingga ke Surabaya. Tapi, rencana proyek kereta cepat ke Surabaya itu perlu didukung oleh adanya transfer teknologi dan pengalaman yang Indonesia telah miliki.

"Karena kita ada hilirisasi, banyak material-material yang akan bisa diproduksi dalam negeri, sehingga dengan demikian menciptakan lapangan kerja buat UMKM dan sebagainya," kata Luhut.

Saat ini, menurutnya, ada sekitar 400-600 orang dari Indonesia sedang menjalani pelatihan di Tiongkok untuk mengoperasikan dan memelihara kereta cepat tersebut. "Ini modal kita nanti, kalau pemerintahan yang akan datang untuk meneruskan program ini. Karena ini akan membuat ekonomi kita lebih baik," kata Luhut.

Lionel Messi mengukuhkan diri sebagai salah satu pesepak bola terbaik sepanjang masa. Kini berusia 35 tahun, berbagai prestasi sudah diraupnya dari lapangan hijau.

Dia memenangkan gelar level klub bersama Barcelona, dan kemudian Paris Saint-Germain. Prestasi pribadi pun dicatat, termasuk tujuh gelar Ballon d'Or.

Messi akhirnya melengkapi capaian dengan berjaya bersama tanah kelahiran. Setelah sempat beberapa kali kandas di final, dia mempersembahkan titel internasional untuk Argentina berupa Copa America 2021. Messi kemudian menambahnya dengan gelar Piala Dunia 2022.

Di balik capaian tersebut, banyak yang lupa dengan noda pada debut Messi. Ya, dia menjadi salah satu pemain yang menerima kartu merah tercepat sepanjang sejarah.

Messi menggantikan Lisandro Lopez pada menit ke-64 laga uji coba melawan Hungaria di Puskas Arena, 17 Agustus 2005. Marca melaporkan, dia baru berada di lapangan selama 40 detik ketika wasit Markus Merk mengganjarnya kartu merah.

Sosok yang selanjutnya bakal membela Inter Miami tersebut diusir karena dianggap melakukan kekerasan terhadap Vilmos Vanczak. Messi kala itu memang bereaksi usai seragamnya ditarik lawan. (Wil_Liputan6.com)

Ketua Tim Investigasi MUI Pusat, Prof Drs H Firdaus Syam mengunjungi Mapolres Indramayu, Jumat (23/6/2023) pagi.

Pada kesempatan itu, MUI terlihat berdiskusi langsung dengan Kapolres Indramayu, AKBP M Fahri Siregar di ruang Patria Tama Polres Indramayu.

Diskusi tersebut guna menggali lebih dalam perihal kontroversi yang terjadi di Al-Zaytun Indramayu dan pemimpinnya Panji Gumilang.

Diketahui ucapan dari Panji Gumilang menimbulkan reaksi yang sangat keras terutama dari kalangan umat Islam.

Mengingat, Ponpes Al-Zaytun dianggap menyebarkan ajarannya yang sesat dan tidak sesuai dengan akidah agama Islam.

"Oleh karena itu kami MUI datang ke Polres Indramayu dalam rangka saling menggali informasi," ujar dia kepada Tribuncirebon.com.

Prof Drs H Firdaus Syam menyampaikan, MUI sendiri sudah memiliki data-data soal apa saja yang menjadi kontroversial di Al Zaytun.

Namun untuk menentukan langkah selanjutnya, MUI perlu penjelasan langsung dari Panji Gumilang sebagai upaya tabayyun.

Hari ini, Panji Gumilang sendiri, kata Prof Drs H Firdaus Syam menyanggupi panggilan dari MUI.

Ia berjanji akan datang ke Gedung Sate, Bandung untuk klarifikasi siang hari nanti.

"Kita harus konfirmasi, ditanyakan dahulu ke yang bersangkutan sehingga kita bisa membuat keputusan yang adil dan sesuai aturan aturan agama dan konstitusi," ujar dia.

Dalam hal ini, Prof Drs H Firdaus Syam turut mengakui MUI banyak mendapat fakta baru seputar Panji Gumilang dan Al-Zaytun.

Namun, fakta tersebut belum bisa disampaikan kepada publik karena harus adanya tabayyun terlebih dahulu.

Lanjut dia, jika memang ada pelanggaran hukum, MUI juga tidak akan tinggal diam.

"Kita ingin bertabayyun dengan pihak yang bersangkutan terlebih dahulu," ujar dia. (*)

Japan's education ministry has drafted provisional guidelines on the use of generative AI at schools, proposing limited use of the technology as a starting point.

The ministry started discussions in May with experts about AI use in schools.

People familiar with the draft guidelines say generative AI use involves concerns about the leak of private information and copyright infringement. They say it would be appropriate for schools to start using such technology on a limited scale, while examining its effective use.

Specifically, the technology could be used to augment viewpoints in group learning stages when opinions are being formulated.

Generative AI is also considered appropriate as an English conversation partner.

But the guidelines say children should not be allowed to freely use the technology before they learn its merits and demerits.

Children should also not use AI to submit works or reports as their own accomplishments. Organizers of contests will be urged to provide sufficient instructions based on their application guidance and themes.

The education ministry says it aims to release the draft of the provisional guidelines by early July after taking experts' opinions into account. It says it will revise the draft in accordance with the latest scientific views.

Source : https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20230622_32/

Masih dalam rangkaian peringatan Hari Lahir Pancasila, Banyuwangi menggelar Festival Generasi Pancasila. Menariknya, festival ini melibatkan ratusan siswa SD, SMP Banyuwangi untuk memperkuat pemahaman dan pengamalan nilai-nilai Pancasila sejak dini. 

Festival tersebut dipusatkan di SMPN 1 Siliragung, Kecamatan Siliragung, Kamis (22/6/2023) dan dihadiri langsung Wakil Bupati Banyuwangi, Sugirah. SMPN 1 Siliragung saat ini didesain menjadi prototype "Sekolah Kebangsaan". 

Festival yang mengusung tema "Gotong Royong Membangun Peradaban dan Pertumbuhan Global" ini diisi beragam kegiatan yang bertujuan penguatan nilai-nilai Pancasila pada generasi muda. 

Festival ini, lanjut dia, menjadi kesempatan yang berharga untuk mengedukasi, menginspirasi, dan membangun kesadaran akan pentingnya Pancasila dalam kehidupan sehari-hari, khususnya kepada generasi muda. 

Ketua panitia kegiatan Festival Pancasila, Alfian menjelaskan festival ini diisi sejumlah kegiatan, di antaranya adalah dialog kebangsaan antar pelajar. (Wil)

Japan's Emperor Naruhito has visited a sand erosion control office in the Special Region of Yogyakarta on the fifth day of his weeklong official visit to Indonesia.

The Emperor headed for Yogyakarta from Jakarta on a Japanese government plane on Wednesday.

Mount Merapi in central Java has claimed many lives through major eruptions.

Japan has long provided technical support to the Sabo Technical Center in Yogyakarta by sending experts to share their know-how on controlling debris flows by building sabo dams.

Sabo literally means "sand protection" in Japanese.

The minister of public works and housing, Basuki Hadimuljono, told the Emperor that the word "sabo" has become well known not only in Indonesia, but also in other countries.

In reply, the Emperor reportedly thanked Indonesia for introducing sabo technology to the world.

Basuki said he is extremely honored and thankful that the Emperor was interested in cooperation between Indonesia and Japan regarding sabo.

Basuki expressed his wish to deepen cooperation between the two countries through sabo as well as politics and culture.

The Emperor also attended a banquet hosted by the governor of Yogyakarta, Sri Sultan Hamengkubuwono X.

He was greeted by the Sultan and his wife at their palace, where he enjoyed a performance of an Indonesian gamelan ensemble and a shadow play.

Source : https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20230622_04/

Wali Kota Banjarmasin, Ibnu Sina membuka sekaligus menjadi Keynote Speaker pada kegiatan Talk Show DILAN (Digital Melayani) Goes To Campus.

Mengangkat tema "Sharing & Caring Public Digital Pemko Banjarmasin", kegiatan yang dihadiri ratusan mahasiswa itu digelar di aula Politeknik Negeri Banjarmasin, Kamis (22/06).

Turut hadir Kepala Diskominfotik, Windiasti Kartika, Direktur Poliban, Joni Riadi, yang juga selaku narasumber beserta seluruh jajaran terkait.

Dalam kesempatan itu, mahasiswa-mahasiswi yang tampak antusias, diperkenalkan dengan Super Apps milik Pemko Banjarmasin. Yaitu Banjarmasin Pintar maupun juga aplikasi layanan tanggap aduan masyarakat SP4N - LAPOR.

Peserta cukup interaktif dengan para narasumber dan banyak memberikan masukan dalam sesi Talkshow tersebut.

Disampaikan Ibnu, DILAN Goes To Campus ini merupakan upaya Pemko Banjarmasin untuk memperkuat basis Smart People lewat perantara adik-adik mahasiswa/i yang merupakan cikal bakal generasi emas kedepan.

Lanjutnya, terlebih mereka sebagai bagian penting dari kolaborasi Pentahelix pilar Akademisi tentu diharapkan dapat menguatkan dan mendorong perwujudan visi misi Banjarmasin Baiman dan Lebih Bermartabat.

"Ini harus dibersamai betul, apalagi erat kaitannya dengan kampus perguruan tinggi yang identik dengan mahasiswa sebagai salah satu pilar kolaborasi pembangunan kota," kata Ibnu.

Petugas Lapas Banyuwangi menangkap basah seorang ustaz berinisial MS yang membawa sabu di Lapas Banyuwangi, Rabu (21/6) sekitar pukul 09.30 WIB. Sabu itu disembunyikan dalam dompetnya.

Kakanwil Kemenkumham Jatim, Imam Jauhari, dalam keterangannya, Rabu (21/6), mengatakan pelaku merupakan tenaga kerohanian di Lapas Banyuwangi. Dia baru mengajar melakukan pembinaan kerohanian di Masjid Lapas Banyuwangi selama tiga kali, tiap hari Rabu.

Sebelumnya ada kecurigaan atas MS karena gelagatnya yang seperti pecandu. Kemudian, saat MS datang ke lapas tadi pagi, petugas melakukan pemeriksaan badan dan barang. Salah satu petugas mencurigai dompet STNK MS yang menonjol. Setelah dibuka ternyata berisi satu klip berisi serbuk kristal sabu. MS langsung dites urine dan hasilnya positif. MS mengaku bahwa barang itu digunakan untuk konsumsi pribadi dan bukan untuk diselundupkan ke dalam Lapas.

Presiden Joko Widodo (Jokowi) seperti disampaikan Menteri Koordinator bidang Kemaritiman dan Investasi, Luhut Binsar Pandjaitan, bakal menjajal Kereta Cepat Jakarta-Bandung (KCJB) sebelum 28 Juli 2023.

"Presiden titip salam ke saudara-saudara sekalian. Beliau akan naik kereta ini nanti sebelum 28 Juli, mungkin satu minggu sebelumnya," kata Luhut di Stasiun Tegalluar, Kabupaten Bandung, Jawa Barat, Kamis (22/6).

Luhut mengatakan proyek KCJB itu pada Juni 2023 ini sudah hampir rampung. Meski begitu, menurutnya, pekerjaan yang dilakukan belum sepenuhnya usai karena masih ada beberapa hal yang perlu diselesaikan. Dia pun menargetkan proyek itu bisa rampung pada 18 Agustus 2023.

Pengamat ekonomi dari STIE YKP Yogyakarta, Aditya Hera Nurmoko, mengatakan selain tekanan inflasi kebutuhan dollar yang cukup besar untuk memenuhi kenaikan utang plafon pemerintahan AS akan menyedot dollar dari seluruh dunia.

"BI semestinya antisipatif, jangan konservatif menahan ketika global sudah naik. Kita masih punya ruang kenaikan suku bunga dari 1,25 persen sampai 3 persen. Capital outflow yang tiba-tiba sangat bahaya, bisa guncang stabilitas sektor keuangan," kata Aditya.

BI, katanya, jangan sampai terlambat merespons, tetapi harus lebih pre-emptive. Bunga acuan BI 5,75 persen sudah tidak masuk akal, harus disesuaikan.

Gubernur the Fed, Jerome Powell, dalam sambutannya pada dengar pendapat setengah tahunan yang diselenggarakan oleh Komite Jasa Keuangan dengan DPR AS di New York, Rabu (21/6), mengatakan tekanan inflasi AS terus menguat sehingga proses untuk menurunkan inflasi ke level 2,0 persen masih jauh.

Menurut statistik yang dikeluarkan Biro Analisis Ekonomi di bawah Departemen Perdagangan AS, selama 12 bulan yang berakhir pada April, harga total pengeluaran konsumsi pribadi (PCE) naik 4,4 persen dari harga PCE inti, tidak termasuk kategori makanan dan energi yang mudah berubah dengan pertumbuhan 4,7 persen dari tahun lalu. Hal itu membuat the Fed lebih sulit menjinakkan inflasi inti karena kebijakan moneter memiliki kendala sendiri.

Pejabat Fed baru-baru ini menaikkan proyeksi inflasi inti untuk 2023 menjadi 3,9 persen, naik dari 3,6 persen, dengan inflasi inti pada 2024 diperkirakan akan bertahan di 2,6 persen.

Pemerintah berencana akan melanjutkan proyek pembangunan Kereta Cepat Jakarta Bandung (KCJB) hingga ke Surabaya, Jawa Timur. 

Hal ini sebagaimana diungkapkan Menteri Koordinator Bidang Kemaritiman dan Investasi (Menko Marves) Luhut Binsar Pandjaitan seusai mengikuti uji coba KCJB dari Stasiun Halim, Jakarta Timur ke Stasiun Tegalluar, Bandung, Kamis (22/6/2023). 

Luhut memastikan dalam proyek lanjutan KCJB ini akan memanfaatkan sumber daya dalam negeri baik untuk tenaga kerjanya maupun material bangunannya.

Pasalnya, pada proyek KCJB sekarang ini pemerintah bekerja sama dengan China untuk melakukan transfer teknologi agar Indonesia dapat meneruskan pembangunan kereta cepat sendiri.

Andromeda Qomariah, Kepala Dinas Koperasi dan UKM Jawa Timur (Jatim) mengatakan kontribusi usaha mikro kecil dan menengah (UMKM) terhadap kinerja ekonomi di wilayah tersebut pada tahun 2022 mencapai 58,36 persen, naik signifikan dibanding tahun 2020 dan 2021.

Menurut Andromeda, kontribusi UMKM pada tahun 2020 mencapai 57,25 persen dan di 2021 naik menjadi 57,71 persen.

тАЬPenyerapan tenaga kerja juga cukup besar, mencapai 96,3 persen. Ini artinya bahwa Kadin Jatim memiliki peran strategis yang menjadi satu bagian dari kolaborasi dalam peningkatan UMKM,тАЭ kata Andromeda, Kamis (23/6/2023)

Dia mengatakan bahwa sinergi permodalan UMKM dengan Kadin Jatim dan Bank UMKM Jatim adalah langkah strategis dalam meningkatkan kinerja UMKM.

Melansir Antara, kata Andromeda, sejauh ini pemerintah telah memberikan dukungan permodalan bagi UMKM melalui berbagai program pendanaan, mulai dari program dana bergulir, maupun melalui Prokesra atau Program Kredit Sejahtera dengan suku bunga 3 persen yang telah diluncurkan tahun lalu dan terus berlanjut di tahun ini.

Jagat media sosial tengah ramai membicarakan dua nama orang terkaya dunia, Elon Musk dan Mark Zuckerberg. 

Bukan persaingan bisnis yang dibicarakan, tetapi adanya wacana duel antara kedua nama tersebut. Wacana itu bermula ketika Elon membuat cuitan yang menyebutkan, dirinya siap berduel dalam ring dengan Mark. 

Cuitan ini merupakan balasan dari serangkaian cuitan terkait rencana Meta mengembangkan aplikasi serupa dengan Twitter.

Pernyataan Elon itu mendapatkan banyak perhatian, bahkan Mark sendiri. Melalui akun Instagram-nya, Mark meminta Elon mengirimkan lokasi pertandingan.

Tidak berselang lama, Elon membalas pernyataan Mark. Bos Tesla itu mengatakan, jika Mark serius dengan pernyataannya, ia siap untuk merealisasikan pertandingan tersebut. (Wil_Kompas.com)

CILEGON┬атАУ 17 paket pekerjaan proyek jalan dengan nilai kerugian negara mencapai Rp1,2 miliar menjadi temuan Badan Pemeriksa Keuangan (BPK) RI Perwakilan Banten, proyek pembangunan jalan itu dikerjakan di tahun anggaran 2022.

Dikatakan Kepala Inspektorat Kota Cilegon Mahmudin bahwa berdasarkan Laporan Hasil Pemeriksaan (LHP) Badan Pemeriksa Keuangan (BPK) RI Perwakilan Banten, terdapat 17 paket proyek jalan yang dilakukan oleh Dinas Pekerjaan dan Penataan Ruang (PUPR) Kota Cilegon.

Temuan itu berupa lebih bayar dan spesifikasi jalan sehingga harus ada pengembalian dari pihak ketiga.

Meski secara keseluruhan nilai tersebut terkesan besar, namun menurut Mahmudin temuan tersebut masih bersifat wajar dikarenakan nilai temuan pada setiap proyeknya terbilang cukup kecil.

Tiga warga negara asing (WNA) yakni Luca Simioni asal Swiss, Barry Pullen dari Inggris, dan Carlo Karol Bonati berkebangsaan Italia melaporkan Puteri Indonesia Persahabatan 2002 Fanni Lauren Christie suaminya WNA asal Italia bernama Valerio Tocci ke Polda Bali. 

Fanni dan suaminya dipolisikan terkait penjualan apartemen di Bali.
Kuasa hukum trio WNA pelapor, Erdia Christina, menjelaskan duduk perkara melaporkan Fanni Lauren Chritie. 

Permasalahan ini terkait dengan apartemen The Double View Mansion (DVM) yang berlokasi di Babadan Nomor 200, Desa Pererenan, Kecamatan Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung.

Sejumlah orang WNA yakni Luca Simioni, Arturo Barone, Thomas Huber, dan Valerio Tocci sepakat untuk membangun apartemen DMV. Pembangunan proyek apartemen tersebut ditawarkan oleh Valerio Tocci beserta fasilitasnya pada 2016 kepada Luca Simioni.

Valerio Tocci kemudian meminta istrinya yakni Fanni Lauren Chritie untuk mendirikan PT Indo Bhali Makmurjaya dalam pembangunan apartemen DVM. Kemudian dalam perjalanannya, keempat WNA itu sepakat untuk berinvestasi. (Wil_Detik.com)

Sekertaris Komisi V DPRD Provinsi Lampung, Mikdar Ilyas mengatakan pihaknya mendapat laporan dari masyarakat Kota Bandar Lampung terkait keluhan masyarakat dalam proses PPDB tahun 2023.

Para wali murid melaporkan terdapat keanehan saat mendampingi anak mereka daftar sekolah, contoh kasus warga Rawa Subur Enggal, Bandar Lampung sesuai zonasi terdekat warga tersebut mendaftarkan anaknya di SMAN 1 Bandar Lampung. 

Siswa tersebut tidak diterima. Anehnya terdapat siswa yang berasal dari daerah Kedamaian, Tanjungkarang Timur justru diterima di SMAN 1 Bandar Lampung. Padahal jarak Rawa Subur ke SMAN 1 Bandar Lampung 800 meter, sementara jarak Kedamaian ke SMAN 1 lebih jauh.

Setelah ditelusuri, ternyata sekolah tidak bisa memberi jawaban yang jelas justru menyerahkan kepada operator untuk menjawab terkait persoalan tersebut.

Petugas Lapas Banyuwangi menangkap basah seorang ustaz berinisial MS yang membawa sabu di Lapas Banyuwangi, Rabu (21/6) sekitar pukul 09.30 WIB. Sabu itu disembunyikan dalam dompetnya.

Kakanwil Kemenkumham Jatim, Imam Jauhari, dalam keterangannya, Rabu (21/6), mengatakan pelaku merupakan tenaga kerohanian di Lapas Banyuwangi. Dia baru mengajar melakukan pembinaan kerohanian di Masjid Lapas Banyuwangi selama tiga kali, tiap hari Rabu.

Sebelumnya ada kecurigaan atas MS karena gelagatnya yang seperti pecandu. Kemudian, saat MS datang ke lapas tadi pagi, petugas melakukan pemeriksaan badan dan barang. Salah satu petugas mencurigai dompet STNK MS yang menonjol. Setelah dibuka ternyata berisi satu klip berisi serbuk kristal sabu. MS langsung dites urine dan hasilnya positif. MS mengaku bahwa barang itu digunakan untuk konsumsi pribadi dan bukan untuk diselundupkan ke dalam Lapas.

Blue Beetle Angel director Manuel Soto recently spoke to Total Film about bringing the film to the DCU and how he sees the future of the characters played in and around Gunn and Safran's shared universe.

The future of the Detective Comics Universe (DCU) is about to change completely. James Gunn and Peter Safran are taking the iconic (and obscure) character in a new direction. The first film in this new universe is The Blue Beetle

Naturally, very little is still known about how the new DCU will come together. James Gunn had previously announced Blue Beetle as "the first DCU character" but noted that Superman: Legacy would be "the first DCU film". The main reason for this appears to be nothing more than the fact that Blue Beetle was conceived before he and Peter Safran assumed their positions as heads of DC Studios. From Soto's comments, it looks like Blue Beetle will remain in this franchise. Hopefully the box office can deliver enough to keep that thought alive.

The five people aboard a missing submersible died in a "catastrophic implosion," a U.S. Coast Guard official said on Thursday, bringing a grim end to the international search for the vessel that was lost during a deep-sea voyage to the wreck of the Titanic, reports Reuters.

"These men were true explorers who shared a distinct spirit of adventure, and a deep passion for exploring and protecting the world's oceans," OceanGate Expeditions, the U.S.-based company that operated the Titan submersible, said in a statement. "Our hearts are with these five souls and every member of their families during this tragic time."

The five aboard included the British billionaire and explorer Hamish Harding, 58; Pakistani-born business magnate Shahzada Dawood, 48, and his 19-year-old son, Suleman, both British citizens; French oceanographer and Titanic expert Paul-Henri Nargeolet, 77, who had visited the wreck dozens of times; and Stockton Rush, the American founder and chief executive of OceanGate, who was piloting the submersible.

Rescue teams from several countries had spent days searching thousands of square miles of open seas with planes and ships for any sign of the 22-foot (6.7-meter) Titan. The submersible lost contact with its support ship on Sunday morning about an hour and 45 minutes into what should have been a two-hour descent.

Kiran Khatri, a resident of Mithi in the Tharparkar district of Sindh, has accomplished a remarkable feat by clearing the Central Superior Service (CSS) exam and securing a position in the inland revenue service. She proudly holds the distinction of being the first woman from Thar and the sole Hindu girl from Tharparkar to pass the exam. In fact, she is the third Hindu girl from across Sindh to achieve this significant milestone.

Originally aspiring to join the police force, Kiran was instead selected for a position in the inland revenue sector. Her training is scheduled to commence in October, and she is eagerly anticipating the substantial responsibilities that will accompany her new role.

Kiran completed her MBBS from Liaquat University of Medical and Health Sciences in Jamshoro in 2020. Following her graduation, she pursued a house job at Civil Hospital, Hyderabad in 2021. She later worked as a lecturer at Indus Medical College, Tando Mohammad Khan.

During her house job, Kiran became acutely aware of the challenges faced by doctors, which motivated her to prepare for the CSS exam. She dedicated herself to studying diligently at her home in Mithi, with the support of her father, who holds the position of deputy director in the education department. Additionally, she utilized online resources such as YouTube to access CSS-related content.

Kiran actively used social media by curating her accounts to focus solely on CSS preparation. She expresses deep gratitude for the unwavering support she received from her parents throughout her journey.

Tharparkar, the largest district in Sindh in terms of area, is home to a population of 1.6 million, with approximately half of the residents being Hindus. Within Sindh's health department, Hindus make up around 30 percent of the medical staff, including a significant number of female doctors.

The exhibits were brought before the court by the candidate of the Labour Party, LP, Mr. Peter Obi, who alleged that the presidential election held on February 25, was rigged in favour of President Bola Tinubu of the ruling All Progressives Congress, APC.

Though ObiтАЩs legal team was led by Dr. Livy Uzoukwu, SAN, the exhibits were, however, tendered through another senior lawyer in the team, Mr. Peter Afuba, SAN.

The petitioners told the court that the exhibits were duly certified by the Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC.

However, the electoral body, through its lawyer, Mr. Kemi Pinhero, SAN, said it was vehemently opposed to the admissibility of the exhibits in evidence.

President Tinubu and the APC, who are the 2nd and 3rd Respondents in the matter, also challenged the admission of the exhibits in evidence.

All the Respondents said they would adduce reasons behind their objections in their final written address.

тАЬPrice levels would always go up. What we have to do is to open up the economy so that people will have more work to do. We need more manufacturing companies in Edo State.тАЭ

тАЬThe gas initiative was launched after a presentation by NIPCO Plc to roll out a pilot scheme to an inter-ministerial team of the Federal Government in 2007.

тАЬNIPCO Gas has established 15 CNG running stations in Benin to provide an alternative for the Gasoline run automobiles,тАЭ he said.

Delivery Agent Karan Ate commemorates his birthday by providing a chocolate with each delivery. As we age, assume responsibilities, and begin working, it becomes exceedingly challenging to even take a day off to celebrate our birthdays. However, we all adapt to changes and learn to commemorate both significant and small occasions within our limited time. The tale of this Zomato delivery guy celebrating his birthday in a remarkably unique manner has captured the hearts of the netizens, who are thoroughly impressed by Karan's touching and heartwarming gesture. Karan's Facebook post sharing the story has gone viral across various social media platforms, with countless individuals already sharing this beautiful account. Karan accompanied the post with the captain, "Today's my birthday, bought a new shirt and distributed chocolates with every order I delivered in Zomato." He also included a mirror selfie showcasing his new shirt and zomato food delivery package sealed with a 5-star chocolate bar.

The desperate search for a missing submersible near the wreck of the Titanic entered a critical juncture on Thursday when air was expected to run out for the five people aboard, but officials vowed to continue scouring the remote North Atlantic.

A remotely operated vehicle deployed from a Canadian vessel to the ocean floor discovered a "debris field" near the Titanic, the US Coast Guard said on Thursday morning on Twitter, adding that experts were "evaluating the information."
Another robot from a French research ship was also sent diving toward the seabed to search for signs of the 22-foot (6.7m) Titan submersible.

The van-sized Titan, operated by US-based OceanGate Expeditions, began what was to be a two-hour descent at 8:00am (1200 GMT) on Sunday but lost contact with its support ship.

The submersible set off with 96 hours of air, according to the company, which means the oxygen would be exhausted by Thursday morning, assuming the Titan is still intact. Precisely when depends on factors such as whether the craft still has power and how calm those on board are, experts say.

Rescuers and relatives of the Titan's five occupants took hope when the US Coast Guard said on Wednesday that Canadian search planes had recorded undersea noises using sonar buoys earlier that day and on Tuesday.

But remote-controlled underwater vehicles searching where the noises were detected did not yield results, and officials cautioned the sounds might not have originated from the Titan.

Kante, known for his dynamic and hardworking style of play, has had an illustrious club career. He won the UEFA Champions League and FIFA Club World Cup with Chelsea, as well as back-to-back Premier League titles with both Leicester City and Chelsea.

The Saudi club has hailed Kante's arrival as one of the most high-profile and impactful signings in their history.

A new study has revealed that plants can efficiently remove toxic fumes and cancer-causing compounds from indoor air and thus, leave you with better air quality in a short time. The findings are being considered ground-breaking as this is the first study to show plants can clean up gasoline vapours. The researchers also showed that indoor plants can eliminate cancer-causing toxins such as benzene.The new study was led by the University of Technology Sydney bioremediation researcher Associate Professor Fraser Torpy, in partnership with Ambius, a plantscaping company. They found that the Ambius small green wall, which contains a mix of indoor plants, effectively removed harmful, cancer-causing pollutants. Notably, it removed 97% of the most toxic compounds from the surrounding air in just eight hours, according to a press statement by the University of Technology Sydney.

Bangladesh has incurred $3.72 billion in economic losses in the last 20 years thanks to climate change, an expert of the Swiss embassy in Dhaka said today.
Bangladesh is the seventh most climate change-vulnerable country in the world and it ranked fifth in the world in terms of such losses, said Syeda Zinia Rashid, senior programme officer of the embassy of Switzerland in Bangladesh.
Around 56 per cent of the country's population or 9 crore people live in "high climate exposure areas", of which 5.3 crore are subject to "very high" exposure, she said.

In Bangladesh, climate change took the highest toll on the agriculture sector, where customised microfinance can be a very effective tool in addressing the risks associated with the impacts of the global warming, Rashid said.

She made the remarks at the closing session of the first phase of Bangladesh Microinsurance Market Development Programme (BMMDP), a programme funded by the Swiss embassy in Bangladesh and anchored by the Financial Institutions Division, finance ministry and the NGO Affairs Bureau of Bangladesh.

The programme was taken to improve farmers' well-being through enhanced agricultural productivity and increased resilience to natural disasters.

The Swiss embassy in association with Swisscontact, an independent and non-profit foundation, organised the event at Sheraton Dhaka hotel, which was attended by Planning Minister MA Mannan as the chief guest.

The BMMDP focuses on developing microinsurance products, conducting research, and enhancing capacity in the microinsurance sector in Bangladesh, Rashid said in a presentation.

More than 1.5 million farmers of 51 districts were reached through the BMMDP activities and 56,000 acres of land were covered under crop insurance, according to the organisers.

Ahead of Bakri Eid, right-wing group Hindu Janajagruti Samiti (HJS) in Chhattisgarh recently launched a statewide campaign calling for a boycott of halal meat.

On June 20, HJS zonal convenor of Chhattisgarh and Maharashtra Sunil Ghanwat while interacting with media persons alleged that Halal-certified products have тАШhijacked the Indian economy.тАЩ

In a video posted on his official Twitter account, he said, тАЬWe demand a halal-free Chhattisgarh. Halal is not limited to meat. It is a marketing strategy which has extended to a global level and gained тАШworldwide 2.1 trillion US dollarsтАЩ in the last nine years.тАЭ

Ghanwat mentions the Organisation of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) and stated that even non-Muslim countries across the world receive halal-certified products.

тАЬThe OIC group consists of 57 Muslim countries. However, OIC has made it clear that meat imported from non-Muslim countries should be halal-certified. And we believe that six NGOs in India are working to provide halal-certified products. Some of them are Jamiat Ulama-i-Hind Halal Trust, Halal India Private Limited,тАЭ Ghanwat told media persons.

Ghanwat further alleged that fast food outlets such as KFC, Mc Donalds, and Pizza Hut are serving halal-certified food in India. тАЬWhy are Hindus forced to eat halal food? They are playing with our sentiments and the Hindu community will oppose it,тАЭ he said.

Halal (an Arabic term meaning permissible/prohibited) meat is mainly consumed by Muslims as it is mandated by their Islamic faith. It should be noted that Hindus do not follow dietary laws related to Halal meat.

Jajaran Satreskrim Polresta Cirebon mengamankan pelaku pengeroyokan dan perusakan asal Indramayu yang berinisial FO (26). Pria yang telah ditetapkan tersangka itu terbukti mengeroyok dan merusak mobil korban di Jalur Gronggong, Desa Kondangsari, Kecamatan Beber, Kabupaten Cirebon.

Kapolresta Cirebon, Kombes Pol Arif Budiman, S.I.K, M.H, melalui Kasat Reskrim, Kompol Anton, S.H, S.I.K, M.H, mengatakan, peristiwa yang mengakibatkan korban mengalami luka-luka akibat pengeroyokan tersebut terjadi pada Sabtu (10/6/2023) kira-kira pukul 16.00 WIB.

тАЬTersangka FO terbukti secara bersama-sama di muka umum melakukan kekerasan dan merusak kendaraan korban. Sehingga korban mengalami luka-luka dan kendaraannya juga mengalami kerusakan di bagian kap serta kacanya pecah,тАЭ kata Kompol Anton, S.H, S.I.K, M.H.

Ia menyampaikan, tersangka dijerat Pasal 170 dan Pasal 406 KUHP dan diancam hukuman maksimal sembilan tahun penjara. Bahkan, dari hasil pemeriksaan sementara diketahui tersangka merupakan residivis kasus serupa dan dijatuhi vonis hukuman selama 1,5 tahun penjara pada tahun 2019.

Penghargaan ini menjadi yang keenam kalinya yang diterima oleh awak kabin Garuda Indonesia, setelah sebelumnya diperoleh pada tahun 2014 тАУ 2018.

Adapun penghargaan diberikan langsung oleh Edward Plaisted CEO Skytrax kepada Irfan Setiaputra Direktur Utama Garuda Indonesia, dalam acara Skytrax World Airline Awards 2023 di Mus├йe de lтАЩAir et de lтАЩEspace (Air and Space Museum), Paris, Prancis, pada Selasa (20/6/2023).

Search operation for the missing Ocean Gate Titan Submarine is still underway. The submersible is carrying five people including a Pakistani Billionaire and his son, a British adventurer, founder of OceanGate, and a French diver.

According to the latest updates, the Titan has crossed the oxygen supply limit of 96 hours, however, there is no confirmed news about its survival. Experts are also predicting that if passengers take measures to conserve breathable air, the oxygen supply period can be extended.

The submarine went missing on Sunday when the US Coast Guard received notification from its command ship that they have lost contact with the vessel. The submersible lost its contact when it was 900 miles east of Cape Cod. As per the news, the OceanGate titan was on its venture to see the remains of Titanic.

A massive search mission is ongoing as the oxygen supply limit has been crossed and the limited supply of ration is expected, making survival difficult.

An unmanned robot integrated into a French research ship is deployed near the wreck of Titanic to facilitate the search operation. In addition, UK Navy Submariner, French Vessel LтАЩ Atalante ROV, and Motor Vessel Horizon Arctic (ROV) are deployed to conduct the search for the lost Titan.

The Higher Education Commission (HEC) has retracted a letter that raised objections to the celebration of the Hindu festival of Holi at a university. The HEC's decision to withdraw the letter came after facing widespread criticism across the country. Salman Sufi, the head of the Prime Minister's Strategic Reforms Unit, clarified that the education minister had instructed the HEC to retract the controversial letter.

In a statement issued by Dr. Shaista Sohail, the executive director of the HEC, it was emphasized that the HEC respects all religions, faiths, and associated festivals celebrated in the country. The HEC clarified that the letter had been misinterpreted and that it did not intend to ban any festivities.

The focus of the HEC's communication was to emphasize academic excellence, research quality, and the development of responsible citizens among the youth. The HEC acknowledged the misinterpretation and withdrew the notification accordingly.

Cabin crew spray the aircraft before take-off, but why do they need to? 

If youтАЩve ever sat on a plane and wondered why cabin crew are spraying the aircraft, there is a very good reason.

Airline workers have a lot of tasks to complete to keep passengers safe and spraying the plane is just one of them. 

Why do they spray the inside of the aircraft?
The process is known as disinsection and is required on flights to and from certain destinations to prevent infectious and contagious diseases, a Civil Aviation Authority spokesman said. ItтАЩs mainly sprayed in countries where diseases are spread by insects, such as malaria and yellow fever.

The reason why is that some countries require aircraft cabins to be sprayed with pesticides to kill insects and stop the spread of diseases such as malaria, Zika, and yellow fever.

Methods used to disinfect the aircraft involve using a World Health Organization-approved non-flammable insecticide that is not harmful to people. Generally, the cabin crew will tell passengers to cover their eyes and spray the insecticide in the air throughout the aircraft cabin, ensuring it circulates to kill any unticketed (insect) guests onboard.

Bangladesh has ranked number one among South Asian countries in terms of gender parity, according to the latest Global Gender Gap Report 2023 by the World Economic Forum (WEF).

With a score of 72.2%, Bangladesh ranked 59th globally, indicating significant progress in achieving gender parity. Women across the country this year experienced a rise in overall gender parity, as reflected in a higher score and index ranking compared to 2022.
Bangladesh ranked 71st globally in 2022 with a gender parity score of 71.4%.

The Global Gender Gap Index annually benchmarks the current state and evolution of gender parity across four key dimensions: Economic Participation and Opportunity, Educational Attainment, Health and Survival, and Political Empowerment.

The level of progress toward gender parity (the parity score) for each indicator is calculated as the ratio of the value of each indicator for women to the value for men.

MC Commissioner Dr Shena Aggarwal launched the
UPID cards at MC suvidha kendra in Zone D and handed over UPID cards to two property owners. MC Additional Commissioner Aaditya Dachalwal, Joint Commissioner Ankur Mahindroo, Zonal Commissioner Jasdev Singh Sekhon, Superintendent Vivek Verma among others were also present on the occasion.
The civic body officials stated that residents can avail the UPID card by paying a nominal fee of Rs 50 at MC suvidha kendras. The residents can get a copy of the card on paper by visiting the MC website (mcludhiana.gov.in) and making online payment.
MC Commissioner Dr Aggarwal said that after getting the UPID card issued, residents will not have to carry the receipts of the payments made to MC in the past as all that record will be available online.
Residents will just have to scan the QR code on the card through a QR code scanner or submit the UPID card number at the suvidha kendras and all the record will be available online.

Penalisis.id тАУ Industri perdagangan dan distribusi memainkan peran yang penting dalam perekonomian suatu negara. Sebagai jembatan antara produsen dan konsumen, industri ini bertanggung jawab atas pengiriman barang dan jasa dari tempat produksi ke pasar. Industri perdagangan dan distribusi tidak hanya melibatkan penjualan dan pengiriman, tetapi juga berbagai kegiatan terkait seperti penyimpanan, pengemasan, dan manajemen rantai pasok.

Perdagangan adalah aktivitas jual beli barang dan jasa antara dua pihak, baik dalam skala lokal maupun internasional. Di era globalisasi saat ini, perdagangan internasional menjadi semakin penting dalam menghubungkan berbagai negara dan memperluas pasar. Melalui industri perdagangan, negara dapat mengimpor barang dan jasa yang tidak diproduksi secara lokal, sementara juga mengeskpor produk unggulan mereka ke pasar internasional.

Facepalm: It might be several years old now, yet thanks to the numerous graphical mods, GTA V still looks stunning. But is it good enough to pass as real life? It certainly fooled one Pakistani politician, who tweeted a clip from the game believing it was actual footage.

On July 5, Pakistan's Awami Tehreek Secretary General, Khurram Nawaz Gandapur, posted a clip from GTA V showing a plane landing and narrowly missing an oil tanker on the runway.

"Narrow escape of an aircraft which could have ended in a great disaster. Miraculous save by the pilot's presence of mind," he wrote in the now-deleted tweet.

As you might imagine, Gandapur was mocked mercilessly after mistaking the clip---the work of YouTube channel The UiGamer---for a real-life incident.

Another Twitter account, Physics-astronomy.org, also appeared to fall into the same trap, calling the video a "Terrorist attack in Algeria," for some reason, which failed because of the "pilot's immense skill."

Gandapur isn't the first person to mix up video games and real life. Back in 2016, the Russian government tweeted an image from Command and Conquer to warn of extremists in Syria, though it did add a "image used for illustration purposes only" disclaimer. In 2017, however, the country's MOD said a screengrab of a promotional video for mobile title AC-130 Gunship Simulator: Special Ops Squadron was "irrefutable evidence" of the US helping ISIS. We've also seen CNN use Fallout 4 to illustrate Russian hacking activities, while in 2018, Russian TV tried to pass off an ARMA 3 clip as actual footage of the Syrian war.

Microsoft today announced its roadmap for building its own quantum supercomputer, using the topological qubits the companyтАЩs researchers have been working on for quite a few years now. 
 
There are still plenty of intermediary milestones to be reached, but Krysta Svore, MicrosoftтАЩs VP of advanced quantum development, told us that the company believes that it will take fewer than 10 years to build a quantum supercomputer using these qubits that will be able to perform a reliable one million quantum operations per second. 
 
ThatтАЩs a new measurement Microsoft is introducing as the overall industry aims to move beyond the current era of noisy intermediate-scale quantum (NISQ) computing. 
 
тАЬWe think about our roadmap and the time to the quantum supercomputer in terms of years rather than decades,тАЭ Svore said. 
Last year, Microsoft announced a major breakthrough when its team first highlighted its ability to create Majorana-based qubits. Majorana qubits have the advantage of being very stable (especially compared to traditional techniques) but they are also extremely difficult to create. 
 
Microsoft made an early bet on this technology and now, a year after first announcing this milestone, the team is publishing a new peer-reviewed paper (in the American Physical SocietyтАЩs Physical Review B) that establishes that it has indeed achieved this first milestone on its way to a quantum supercomputer. To get to this point, Microsoft showed results from more devices and far more data than a year ago when it first announced this work.

Ribuan massa aksi dari Forum Solidaritas Dharma Ayu mulai berdatangan ke gerbang utama  Ponpes Al Zaytun, Kamis (22/6/2023).

Massa aksi datang pukul 12.30 WIB sembari menggemakan sholawat.

Demo yang mereka lakukan diketahui soal dugaan penyimpangan agama yang terjadi di dalam pondok pesantren.

Di sisi lain, aksi ini sekaligus untuk mengusut dugaan terafiliasinya  Ponpes Al Zaytun dengan Negara Islam Indonesia (NII).

Mereka meminta agar pimpinan Ponpes Al Zaytun Panji Gumilang diadili sesuai hukum yang berlaku.

Pantauan Tribuncirebon.com, lantunan sholawat yang dilantunkan massa aksi dibalas dengan bacaan doa dari ribuan massa lainnya yang ada di dalam pondok pesantren.

Seorang pemotor membuat onar di halaman salah satu rumah sakit yang berada di Jalan Raya Cikunir, Singaparna, Kabupaten Tasikmalaya.

Dalam rekaman berdurasi 1 menit 31 detik, terlihat seorang pemotor yang membonceng anaknya tiba-tiba masuk area rumah sakit.

Pemotor tersebut kemudian menabrakan motornya ke pinggir bangku yang berada di depan pintu masuk rumah sakit itu. Ironisnya lagi, terlihat sang anak yang mengenakan pelindung kepala sempat terguncang saat berdiri di sela-sela stang dan kursi duduk.

Tak hanya itu, pelaku kemudian menyerang petugas keamanan yang menegurnya. Meski berusaha ditenangkan, pemotor itu kembali memukul petugas keamanan hingga direlai pengunjung rumah sakit. Sang anak turut menyaksikan kekerasan yang terjadi.

Mengetahui adanya kejadian tersebut, polisi bergerak melakukan penelusuran. Polisi juga telah menerima laporan dari pihak rumah sakit soal adanya peristiwa tersebut.

"Malam kita nerima laporan, dan sekarang anggota lagi di lapangan," kata AKP Ari Rinaldo, Kasat Reskrim Polres Tasikmalaya pada detikJabar, Kamis (22/6/23).

Pihaknya belum menjelaskan motif dan identitas pelaku yang sempat terekam kamera CCTV. Saat ini pihaknya masih melakukan penyelidikan dan memburu pelaku.

Condemning PTI confrontational policy, Ghulam Sarwar parts ways with party

Ghulam Sarwar Khan, a senior leader of Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) and former aviation minister, has parted ways with the party due to the violent protests on May 9. He strongly condemned the party's confrontational policy towards state institutions and demanded punishment for the rioters who attacked defense and public installations. Sarwar emphasized the sacrifices made by Pakistan's forces for the country's survival and condemned the attacks on sensitive locations. He expressed his disagreement with the party's confrontational policy and stated that institutions should not be fought against. Sarwar's statement came after his arrest in Islamabad for his alleged involvement in the May 9 protests. Several other PTI leaders, including Fawad Chaudhry, Imran Ismail, Shireen Mazari, Ali Zaidi, and Aamir Mehmood Kiani, have also left the party following the violent protests.

Sheikh Hamdan bin Mohammed, Crown Prince of Dubai, on Monday approved various projects to support the Dubai Economic Agenda D33 strategy and boost the emirateтАЩs competitiveness and future-readiness.

The projects, approved during a meeting of the Executive Council, include a centennial sewerage system, which will include an investment of Dh80 billion ($21.8 billion), and the adoption of a new model to boost small and medium enterprises in Dubai, the Dubai Media Office said in a statement.

The centennial sewerage system aims to be among тАЬthe worldтАЩs most advanced and sustainableтАЭ infrastructure projects and has been designed to serve the needs of the population for the next 100 years, in alignment with the D33 agenda and the Dubai Urban Plan 2040.

Prankster Nadir Ali faces backlash over religious conversion question to actress.

Nadir Ali, a popular YouTuber, is currently facing significant backlash across various social media platforms for his controversial conduct during a podcast interview with model Sunita Marshall. The online community has criticized Ali for his inappropriate and intrusive questioning, which has ignited a wave of negative sentiment.

During the interview, Ali placed Marshall in an uncomfortable position by delving into personal and sensitive matters regarding her religious choices. This line of questioning was highly inappropriate, given the delicate nature of the topic. Despite the potential for discomfort, Marshall, who is married to Muslim actor Hassan Ahmed while being a Christian herself, responded gracefully, stating that she has no intentions of converting to Islam. However, Ali persisted, further fanning the flames of criticism by remarking, "May Almighty show you the right path."

The actions of Ali have drawn strong condemnation from both social media users and prominent figures in the entertainment industry. They emphasize that matters of faith and religious choices should not be brought up on a public platform due to their deeply personal and sensitive nature. Many individuals expressed their solidarity with Marshall, while also denouncing Ali for intentionally generating controversy through his inappropriate line of questioning.

Actor Nadia Afghan referred to Ali's behavior as disgraceful, while model Mathira openly expressed her disapproval and sense of shame regarding the host's actions. These sentiments reflect the widespread disapproval and disappointment that has engulfed social media in response to Ali's conduct.
